Kubernetes Disaster Recovery
│
├─ 1. Objectives
│   ├─ Minimize Downtime (RTO)
│   ├─ Minimize Data Loss (RPO)
│   ├─ Ensure Business Continuity
│   └─ Maintain Compliance & Auditability
│
├─ 2. Backup & Restore
│   ├─ etcd Backups
│   │   ├─ Tool: etcdctl snapshot
│   │   └─ Function: Takes cluster state snapshot; can restore etcd on failure
│   ├─ Persistent Volume Backups
│   │   ├─ Tool: CSI VolumeSnapshot
│   │   │   └─ Function: Creates snapshot of PVs, supports restore
│   │   ├─ Tool: Cloud Provider Snapshots (AWS EBS, GCP PD, Azure Disk)
│   │   │   └─ Function: Off-cluster storage and quick restore
│   ├─ Cluster Configuration Backup
│   │   ├─ Tool: kubectl / kustomize / GitOps (ArgoCD, Flux)
│   │   │   └─ Function: Export manifests for redeployment
│   └─ Full DR Tools
│       ├─ Velero
│       │   ├─ Backup: Cluster state + PVs
│       │   ├─ Restore: Namespace, cluster, or PV restore
│       │   └─ Migration: Move workloads across clusters
│       ├─ Kasten K10
│       │   ├─ Backup: Application-level & PVs
│       │   ├─ Restore: Point-in-time restore
│       │   └─ Disaster Recovery Orchestration
│       └─ Stash by AppsCode
│           ├─ Backup: PV + resources
│           └─ Restore: Supports scheduled restore
│
├─ 3. Multi-Cluster / Multi-Region Setup
│   ├─ Active-Active
│   │   ├─ Tool: Istio / Linkerd for global service routing
│   │   └─ Function: Synchronous replication and load balancing
│   ├─ Active-Passive
│   │   ├─ Tool: Velero / Kasten K10
│   │   └─ Function: Failover to standby cluster using backups
│   └─ Cluster Federation
│       ├─ Tool: KubeFed
│       └─ Function: Synchronize resources across clusters
│
├─ 4. Application Recovery Strategies
│   ├─ Stateful Applications
│   │   ├─ Tool: Database native replication (MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB)
│   │   └─ Function: Keep data in sync across regions
│   ├─ Stateless Applications
│   │   ├─ Tool: GitOps (ArgoCD, Flux)
│   │   └─ Function: Redeploy manifests automatically
│   └─ Configuration & Secrets
│       ├─ Tool: HashiCorp Vault / AWS KMS / Sealed Secrets
│       └─ Function: Restore encrypted secrets and configuration
│
├─ 5. Automation & Orchestration
│   ├─ DR Playbooks / Runbooks
│   ├─ Automated Failover
│   │   ├─ Tool: ExternalDNS / Cloud Load Balancer
│   │   └─ Function: Automatically switch traffic to healthy cluster
│   └─ Health Checks & Monitoring
│       ├─ Tool: Prometheus + Grafana
│       └─ Function: Alert on node/cluster failures
│
├─ 6. Testing & Validation
│   ├─ Regular DR Drills
│   ├─ Simulated Failures
│   ├─ Test restore from backups
│   └─ Validate RTO / RPO targets
│
└─ 7. Best Practices
    ├─ Keep off-cluster backups
    ├─ Automate recovery steps
    ├─ Encrypt backup data
    ├─ Document DR procedures
    ├─ Version manifests for easy redeployment
    └─ Monitor recovery readiness continuously
